50|$|Other {{examples}} include the coverage of 'missing white woman syndrome' stories like those of <b>Chandra</b> <b>Levy,</b> Elizabeth Smart, Laci Peterson. Critics claim that news executives are only boosting rating with these stories, which only impact a select few, instead of broadcasting national issues.|$|E
5000|$|Gary Condit (B.A., 1972) - former Congressman from California. He is most {{noted for}} his affair with <b>Chandra</b> <b>Levy,</b> which was exposed after Levy's disappearance. Condit was later cleared of Levy's murder and Ingmar Guandique {{was arrested in}} {{connection}} with Levy murder.|$|E
